<p class="mt-3">
    <code>HBEditForm</code> wraps Blazor's <code>EditForm</code> and adds three things on top of the
    standard model/validation flow: an optional <code>Validation</code> delegate for cross-field
    rules that data annotations can't express (returning a dictionary of field names to error
    messages, which are surfaced through the usual <code>&lt;ValidationMessage&gt;</code>),
    strongly-typed <code>OnValidSubmit</code>/<code>OnInvalidSubmit</code> callbacks that receive
    the model, and <code>DisableWhileSubmitting</code>, which disables the form while an async
    submit is in flight. The child content receives the form itself as context, so controls can
    read <code>IsSubmitting</code> to reflect that state.
</p>

